$ Shell command: chmod
@ chmod

`chmod` changes the file mode bits.

{ Changing files to 644, directories to 755

  Uppercase X (`+X`) set the executable bit for directories only.
 
code {
chmod -R a=r,u+w,a+X /path/to/directory
code }


}

